    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, carefully add your<strong> black mustard seeds</strong> and <strong>coriander seeds</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant, then transfer to a heat proof bowl and set aside for later, reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es] </strong>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook on both sides for 3 min or until browned</p><p>Add the <strong>browned chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), reserve the pan and put under the grill for 10-12 min or until charred, caramelised and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>grilled chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic & ginger</strong>, <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>toasted mustard & coriander seeds </strong>with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>choila sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>grilled chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks - this technique is known as 'pulling'</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>shredded chicken</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped tomato</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and most of your <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) to the pan with the <strong>choila sauce</strong></p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime[s]</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix \u2013 this is your <strong>Nepalese-style chicken choila</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nepalese-style-chicken-breast-choila-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Nepalese-style chicken choila</strong> on top of the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining coriander</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
